"Information warfare (IW) where countries attacks enemies electronically with computers, is likely to be actively used today, especially by China. IW has been around since the 1990s. Although it was deemed to be the next big thing in computers, the speciality hasn't exploded as expected. Since September 11, these more subtle forms of attack have been overshadowed by the ‘war against terrorism.’ However, there have been may recent cases where information warfare has been used. Many of these cases involved China in one way or the other. Also, earlier this year the UK National Infrastructure Security Coordination Centre (NISCC) issued a warning about a plethora of information warfare attacks from Asia targeting big companies. Information warfare had definitely matured. Indeed it was used by the UK in the recent war on Iraq and many US Government departments carry it out as part of their duties. But, nevertheless, it could suffer from a lack of credibility on the actual battlefield… This article brings to light the level of activity of information warfare today. It is an underground threat that is ongoing between countries. And China is one of the biggest perpetrators."
